00092 /* Macros for declaring and implementing type-safe wrappers for LHASH callbacks.
00093  * This way, callbacks can be provided to LHASH structures without function
00094  * pointer casting and the macro-defined callbacks provide per-variable casting
00095  * before deferring to the underlying type-specific callbacks. NB: It is
00096  * possible to place a "static" in front of both the DECLARE and IMPLEMENT
00097  * macros if the functions are strictly internal. */
00098 
00099 /* First: "hash" functions */
00100 #define DECLARE_LHASH_HASH_FN(f_name,o_type) \
00101     unsigned long f_name##_LHASH_HASH(const void *);
00102 #define IMPLEMENT_LHASH_HASH_FN(f_name,o_type) \
00103     unsigned long f_name##_LHASH_HASH(const void *arg) { \
00104         o_type a = (o_type)arg; \
00105         return f_name(a); }
00106 #define LHASH_HASH_FN(f_name) f_name##_LHASH_HASH
00107 
00108 /* Second: "compare" functions */
00109 #define DECLARE_LHASH_COMP_FN(f_name,o_type) \
00110     int f_name##_LHASH_COMP(const void *, const void *);
00111 #define IMPLEMENT_LHASH_COMP_FN(f_name,o_type) \
00112     int f_name##_LHASH_COMP(const void *arg1, const void *arg2) { \
00113         o_type a = (o_type)arg1; \
00114         o_type b = (o_type)arg2; \
00115         return f_name(a,b); }
00116 #define LHASH_COMP_FN(f_name) f_name##_LHASH_COMP
00117 
00118 /* Third: "doall" functions */
00119 #define DECLARE_LHASH_DOALL_FN(f_name,o_type) \
00120     void f_name##_LHASH_DOALL(const void *);
00121 #define IMPLEMENT_LHASH_DOALL_FN(f_name,o_type) \
00122     void f_name##_LHASH_DOALL(const void *arg) { \
00123         o_type a = (o_type)arg; \
00124         f_name(a); }
00125 #define LHASH_DOALL_FN(f_name) f_name##_LHASH_DOALL
00126 
00127 /* Fourth: "doall_arg" functions */
00128 #define DECLARE_LHASH_DOALL_ARG_FN(f_name,o_type,a_type) \
00129     void f_name##_LHASH_DOALL_ARG(const void *, void *);
00130 #define IMPLEMENT_LHASH_DOALL_ARG_FN(f_name,o_type,a_type) \
00131     void f_name##_LHASH_DOALL_ARG(const void *arg1, void *arg2) { \
00132         o_type a = (o_type)arg1; \
00133         a_type b = (a_type)arg2; \
00134         f_name(a,b); }
00135 #define LHASH_DOALL_ARG_FN(f_name) f_name##_LHASH_DOALL_ARG
